=======================ABOUT=========================
"Cymbalki" - Glockenspiel in english.  It is software made
for educational purposes.
How to use it?  In “piosenki” directory are files with 
encoded melodies.  In Cymbalki program you can select
one of these melodies and “play” it.  Playing means 
showing to each musician (up to 5 musicians can play 
simultaneously) when to play each note.

Cymbalki don’t measure musicians performance, it only 
displays melodies by 2D animations.

To start program run cymbalki.sh (linux) or cymbalki.bat (windows)

=======================CONFIG FILE========================

In conf.txt file you can set:

fullscreen – 0 means program will run in window and 1 means 
	application will run in fullscreen mode

width – resolution of program window is 3/4*width X width

background – 0 means background image is not displayed 1 otherwise

soundNames – 0 means sound names are not displayed 1 otherwise


